{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct contains a table of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsRef"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"running the idle function).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call doesn’t block too long"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and miss the next timeout.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"since it must wait until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been called before it knows whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call blocks. In the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"check function, it tests the results of the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call to see if the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"required condition has been met, and returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference to an existing ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]},{"name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","type":"aside"}]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","title":"SourceFuncsRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib14SourceFuncsRefV","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"struct"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-1il83","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-5idr3","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-891i5","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-937im","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(_:)-9qm49","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef\/init(opaquePointer:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GL